# Getting Started with charmed_rust WASM

## Installation

### Using npm (recommended)

\`\`\`bash
npm install @charmed/wasm
# or
yarn add @charmed/wasm
# or
pnpm add @charmed/wasm
\`\`\`

### Using CDN

\`\`\`html
<script type="module">
  import init, { Style, newStyle } from 'https://unpkg.com/@charmed/wasm@latest';

  await init();

  const styled = newStyle()
    .foreground("#ff6b6b")
    .bold()
    .render("Hello from CDN!");

  document.body.innerHTML = styled;
</script>
\`\`\`

## Basic Usage

### Creating Styles

\`\`\`javascript
import init, { newStyle } from '@charmed/wasm';

// Initialize the WASM module (required once)
await init();

// Create a new style
const style = newStyle()
  .foreground("#61dafb")    // Text color
  .background("#282c34")    // Background color
  .bold()                   // Bold text
  .padding(1, 2, 1, 2);     // top, right, bottom, left

// Render styled content
const html = style.render("Styled Text");

// Insert into DOM
document.getElementById('output').innerHTML = html;
\`\`\`

### Working with Colors

\`\`\`javascript
import { Color } from '@charmed/wasm';

// Hex colors
const red = Color.fromHex("#ff0000");

// RGB colors
const green = Color.fromRgb(0, 255, 0);

// ANSI colors (0-255)
const blue = Color.fromAnsi(12);
\`\`\`

### Layout Functions

\`\`\`javascript
import { joinHorizontal, joinVertical } from '@charmed/wasm';

const left = newStyle().background("#ff6b6b").render("Left");
const right = newStyle().background("#4ecdc4").render("Right");

// Side by side
const horizontal = joinHorizontal([left, right]);

// Stacked
const vertical = joinVertical([left, right]);
\`\`\`
```

